{"session_id": "1f07b1a6-2264-45e6-8265-3ec6390be07f", "task": "This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user wanted to refactor the pr-watch skill in their Claude Code plugin from a blocking `sleep 120` polling loop to an event-driven approach using the Monitor tool. They wanted PR events (review comments, CI failures, PR state changes) detected via a background Monitor script that emits structured events, with Claude reacting to those events. Key sub-requests included:\n   - Investigate alternatives to polling and webhooks (consulted Codex and Gemini MCPs)\n   - Use 60-second polling interval (changed from initial 30s)\n   - Set absolute timeout to 60 minutes (changed from initial 120min)\n   - Auto-resolve conflicts instead of stopping monitoring\n   - Decided NOT to use `gh pr checks --watch`\n   - Create a PR, bump versions, then monitor the PR for review/CI fixes\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Claude Code Monitor tool: background script where each stdout line becomes a notification, `persistent: true` for session-length watches, `timeout_ms` ignored when persistent\n   - GitHub has no official streaming/SSE/GraphQL Subscriptions for PR events\n   - Activity Events API + ETag for efficient polling (304 Not Modified saves rate limits)\n   - `gh pr checks --watch` for CI-specific watching (exits on completion, not suitable for persistent monitoring)\n   - Event-driven architecture: Monitor script detects state changes \u2192 emits structured events \u2192 Claude reacts\n   - Conventional Commits with commitlint (scope-enum: caffeine, catch-up, claude, dev, git, hookify)\n   - Plugin version management: plugin.json + marketplace.json synchronized updates\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - `plugins/git/skills/pr-watch/SKILL.md` (PRIMARY FILE)\n     - This is the main skill definition that was completely rewritten from polling to Monitor-based\n     - Key structural changes: sleep loop \u2192 Monitor", "stage": "apply", "user_decision": "approve", "edit_distance": 0.0, "user_feedback_text": "", "change_type": "unknown", "turn_number": 419, "_swechat_pushback": null, "_swechat_persona": "expert_nitpicker", "_swechat_mode": "collaborative", "_swechat_intent": null, "_swechat_success": "88.0", "_swechat_agent_pct": null}
